Description: Body sherd of North Ionian black-figured pottery dinos or krater; interior reserved; exterior: two friezes separated by band with added red band lined in white; above, perhaps tongues; below, most of rear of sphinx to left, with added red; rosettes and blobs as fill. Graffito on exterior.
Curator's comments: The piece is close to 1886,0401.946, but the difference in thickness suggests that they are not from the same piece.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.634)
